infinite loops caused by not compiling V8 style

This test checks, among other things, that the implementation compiles regular expressions lazily, which is not mandated by the spec. It also checks whether a specific regular expression triggers a stack overflow during its compilation, which is heavily dependent on the implementation (e.g. TRegex's parser has its own stack). It also calls gc after the test, which is V8-specific.

RegExp: Performance test. Tests for a specific optimization made by V8's Irregexp, in which patterns of the form (ab|ac|z|ad|ae|af) are optimized into patterns of the form (a[b-f]|z). Due to the size of the pattern involved, TRegex bails out during parsing (https://bugs.chromium.org/p/chromium/issues/detail?id=482998).
